# Vehicle Damage Detection — End-to-End Modular Pipeline

## Goal

Build a production-ready, modular vehicle damage detection pipeline based on the [existing plan](file:///D:/vehicle-detection/docs/Vehicle_Damage_Detection_Implementation_Plan.md). The key design goal is **strategy-swappability**: each stage of the pipeline (gatekeeper, damage segmentation, part segmentation) uses a pluggable training strategy so you can experiment with different architectures, hyperparameters, and training techniques — then compare results side-by-side — without rewriting pipeline code.

---

## Review of Existing Plan

The original document specifies a solid 3-stage architecture:

| Stage | Role | Default Model |
|-------|------|---------------|
| **Gatekeeper** | Binary classification (car present + damaged?) | ResNet50 / MobileNet |
| **Damage Localization** | Instance segmentation of damage types | Mask R-CNN (ResNet50-FPN) |
| **Car Part Mapping** | Instance segmentation of car parts | Mask R-CNN / YOLACT |
| **Orchestrator** | IoU overlap to map damage → part | Python logic |

**Strengths:** Clear separation of concerns, pixel-level masks for cost estimation, modular retraining.

**Gaps this plan addresses:**
- No experiment tracking or strategy abstraction — hard to compare different approaches
- No configuration management — hyperparameters are hardcoded
- No data versioning or validation pipeline
- No evaluation harness for systematic comparison
- No reproducibility infrastructure (seeds, logging, checkpointing)
- Training code is monolithic — changing the model requires rewriting the training loop

