### Component 2: Model Registry & Strategy Pattern

This is the core modularity mechanism. Every model is a class that inherits from a base and registers itself. The training loop doesn't know which model it's training — it just calls the interface.

#### [NEW] [base.py](file:///D:/vehicle-detection/src/models/base.py)

```python
from abc import ABC, abstractmethod

class BaseDetector(ABC):
    """Abstract base for all detection/segmentation models."""

    @abstractmethod
    def build(self, config: dict) -> torch.nn.Module:
        """Construct and return the model."""
        ...

    @abstractmethod
    def get_transform(self, is_train: bool):
        """Return data transforms specific to this model."""
        ...

    @abstractmethod
    def compute_loss(self, model, images, targets) -> dict:
        """Forward pass + loss computation. Returns loss dict."""
        ...

    @abstractmethod
    def post_process(self, predictions, confidence_threshold: float) -> list:
        """Post-process raw model outputs into standardized format."""
        ...


class BaseClassifier(ABC):
    """Abstract base for gatekeeper classification models."""

    @abstractmethod
    def build(self, config: dict) -> torch.nn.Module:
        ...

    @abstractmethod
    def predict(self, model, image) -> dict:
        ...
```

#### [NEW] [registry.py](file:///D:/vehicle-detection/src/models/registry.py)

```python
MODEL_REGISTRY = {}

def register_model(name):
    def decorator(cls):
        MODEL_REGISTRY[name] = cls
        return cls
    return decorator

def get_model(name):
    if name not in MODEL_REGISTRY:
        raise ValueError(f"Model '{name}' not in registry. Available: {list(MODEL_REGISTRY.keys())}")
    return MODEL_REGISTRY[name]
```

