## How Strategy Swapping Works in Practice

Here's a concrete example of how you'd experiment with different approaches:

### Experiment 1: Baseline Mask R-CNN (ResNet50)
```bash
python scripts/train.py --config configs/damage/maskrcnn_resnet50.yaml
# → runs/damage_maskrcnn_resnet50_v1/
```

### Experiment 2: Swap backbone to Swin Transformer
```bash
python scripts/train.py --config configs/damage/maskrcnn_swin.yaml
# → runs/damage_maskrcnn_swin_v1/
```

### Experiment 3: Try YOLOv8 segmentation entirely
```bash
python scripts/train.py --config configs/damage/yolov8_seg.yaml
# → runs/damage_yolov8_seg_v1/
```

### Experiment 4: Same model, different training strategy
```bash
python scripts/train.py --config configs/damage/maskrcnn_resnet50.yaml \
    --set training.optimizer.name=adamw training.scheduler.name=cosine training.epochs=60
# → runs/damage_maskrcnn_resnet50_adamw_cosine/
```

### Compare all
```bash
python scripts/compare.py --runs damage_maskrcnn_resnet50_v1 damage_maskrcnn_swin_v1 damage_yolov8_seg_v1
